[There have been several reports of malaria in
Mumbai in 2010, and it seems that malaria has
been reintroduced in Mumbai and transmission is
established from a local reservoir in the city.
Of note, according to the world malaria report
2009 map of malaria in India, the state
Maharastra, is classified as low risk with less
than or equal to one case per 1000 inhabitants per year. - Mod.EP]

[The interactive HealthMap/ProMED map for Mumbai,
India, is available at: <http://healthmap.org/r/00BT> - CopyEd.EJP]
